Issue #161: Wrong paralle NOR setting

Title: Wrong paralle NOR setting

Body:
1. Reproduce the problem:
- Write data to parallel NOR.
- Walk through the NOR, reading each byte twice then compare. Check for mismatch. This is the code I use:


        int idx = 0;
        int loop = 0;
        while(1)
        {            
            uint8_t norValue1 = *((volatile uint8_t*)0x60000000 + idx);
            uint8_t norValue2 = *((volatile uint8_t*)0x60000000 + idx);

            if ( norValue1 != norValue2)
                printf("1: %x %x %x %x\r\n", loop, idx, norValue1, norValue2);

            ++idx;
            if (idx == 0xC00000)
            {
                idx = 0;
                ++loop;
            }   
        }


2. Cause. The current setting sets the read cycle exactly at 70ns. The problem is the tACC of the NOR has a maximum value of 70ns. If that happens, the FMC will not have time to sample valid data.

3. The fix: lengthen the cycle. In my code, I set "DataSetupTime" to 6 instead of 5. This is my code:


  /* Asyncronuous. Timing configuration derived from HCLK = 200MHz (5ns period). */
  Timing.AddressSetupTime      = 9;
  Timing.AddressHoldTime       = 1 /* don't care */;
  Timing.DataSetupTime         = 6;
  Timing.BusTurnAroundDuration = 4;
  Timing.CLKDivision           = 4 /* don't care */;
  Timing.DataLatency           = 2 /* don't care */;
  Timing.AccessMode            = FMC_ACCESS_MODE_B;

