Issue #144: Wrong pin config in stm32h747i_eval_nor.c

Title: Wrong pin config in stm32h747i_eval_nor.c

Body:
I reported this in #142 and #143, but they were closed without any effort from ST to discuss. It's a nasty bug that took me a few days to figure out; so please fix it.

This is in the current code:

/* GPIOC configuration */
  gpio_init_structure.Alternate = GPIO_AF9_FMC;
  gpio_init_structure.Pin   = GPIO_PIN_6 | GPIO_PIN_7;
  HAL_GPIO_Init(GPIOC, &gpio_init_structure);

  /* GPIOD configuration */
  gpio_init_structure.Alternate = GPIO_AF12_FMC;  //add GPIO_PIN_7
  gpio_init_structure.Pin   = GPIO_PIN_0 | GPIO_PIN_1 | GPIO_PIN_4 | GPIO_PIN_5|GPIO_PIN_7|\
                              GPIO_PIN_8 | GPIO_PIN_9 | GPIO_PIN_10 | GPIO_PIN_11 |\
                              GPIO_PIN_12 | GPIO_PIN_13 | GPIO_PIN_14 | GPIO_PIN_15;
  HAL_GPIO_Init(GPIOD, &gpio_init_structure);

What's wrong is PC6 and PC7 are not used for FMC in stm32h747i_eval (they're used for other purposes according to the board document), so they need to be removed here, and clock for GPIOC doesn't need to be turned on. Then GPIO_PIN_6 needs to be added to GPIOD init. So replace the above code with this:


/* GPIOD configuration */
  gpio_init_structure.Alternate = GPIO_AF12_FMC;
  gpio_init_structure.Pin   = GPIO_PIN_0 | GPIO_PIN_1 | GPIO_PIN_4 | GPIO_PIN_5| GPIO_PIN_6| GPIO_PIN_7|\
                              GPIO_PIN_8 | GPIO_PIN_9 | GPIO_PIN_10 | GPIO_PIN_11 |\
                              GPIO_PIN_12 | GPIO_PIN_13 | GPIO_PIN_14 | GPIO_PIN_15;
  HAL_GPIO_Init(GPIOD, &gpio_init_structure);

