Hi @RKOUSTM,
I apologize, let me few days in order to prepare a project to show you the problem.

With regards,

[GiulioDallaVecchia - 2021-05-17T05:27:08Z]
Hi @RKOUSTM,
when a user calls BSP_OSPI_NOR_Erase_Chip inside stm32h735g_discovery_ospi.c should be better to wait until the erasing operation will be finisched (as you handle with other driver). Without that the function returns immedeatly seeming that everythings is done. I suggest to modify that function in this way:


int32_t BSP_OSPI_NOR_Erase_Chip(uint32_t Instance)
{
  int32_t ret;

  /* Check if the instance is supported */
  if(Instance >= OSPI_NOR_INSTANCES_NUMBER)
  {
    ret = BSP_ERROR_WRONG_PARAM;
  }
  else
  {
    /* Check Flash busy ? */
    if(MX25LM51245G_AutoPollingMemReady(&hospi_nor[Instance], Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].InterfaceMode, Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].TransferRate) != MX25LM51245G_OK)
    {
      ret = BSP_ERROR_COMPONENT_FAILURE;
    }/* Enable write operations */
    else if(MX25LM51245G_WriteEnable(&hospi_nor[Instance], Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].InterfaceMode, Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].TransferRate) != MX25LM51245G_OK)
    {
      ret = BSP_ERROR_COMPONENT_FAILURE;
    }/* Issue Chip erase command */
    else if(MX25LM51245G_ChipErase(&hospi_nor[Instance], Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].InterfaceMode, Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].TransferRate) != MX25LM51245G_OK)
    {
      ret = BSP_ERROR_COMPONENT_FAILURE;
    }
    /* Check Flash busy ? */
    if(MX25LM51245G_AutoPollingMemReady(&hospi_nor[Instance], Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].InterfaceMode, Ospi_Nor_Ctx[Instance].TransferRate) != MX25LM51245G_OK)
    {
      ret = BSP_ERROR_COMPONENT_FAILURE;
    }
    else
    {
      ret = BSP_ERROR_NONE;
    }
  }

  /* Return BSP status */
  return ret;
}


With the last autopolling mem ready you should wait at least for the chip erasing time or at least advice the user that have to check the status of memory after every erasing operation

